Event.0: Egyptian scholar and statesman Boutros Boutros-Ghali—who, as UN secretary-general (1992–96), vigorously supported UN mediation in post-Cold War strife and oversaw lengthy and difficult peacekeeping operations in several war-torn countries—died at age 93.
Event.1: The Kyoto Protocol, an international treaty aimed at reducing the emission of gases that contribute to global warming, went into effect.
Event.2: The NHL became the first North American professional sports league to cancel an entire season; the 2004–05 season was canceled after the collective-bargaining agreement between the owners and the players' union ran out.
Event.3: The Kyoto Protocol comes into force following its ratification by Russia.
